# NeuroCode вЂ” Agentic VS Code Extension
# Cursor Rules File v2.0 вЂ” AI Constitution for this Project
# Author: ZMS Digital Solutions вЂ” Dhaka, Bangladesh
# Stack: TypeScript + Node.js Sidecar + React WebView + OpenAI Gateway / Ollama
# Acquisition Target: Google / Meta / SpaceX / GitHub

## PROJECT IDENTITY

You are building **NeuroCode** вЂ” a VS Code extension that enables agentic coding on low-end GPUs
by intelligently splitting codebases into small context shards and routing them through local or
remote LLMs. This is NOT a wrapper around Copilot. It is a ground-up agentic system built for
acquisition вЂ” every architectural decision must create a defensible moat.

Three moats being built simultaneously:
1. **The Shard Architecture** вЂ” runs agentic coding on 4GB VRAM (technical moat)
2. **The Edit Genome** вЂ” opt-in dataset of human-verified code edits (data moat)
3. **Air-Gap Mode** вЂ” the only agentic coder that works in classified/regulated environments (market moat)

---

## FULL ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW

The system has 3 main processes plus 2 background subsystems:

```
[VS Code Extension Host]  в†ђв†’  [Sidecar Node.js Server :39291]  в†ђв†’  [LLM Backend]
   TypeScript                    CodeGraph                            OpenAI Gateway / Ollama
   WebView React UI              ShardManager                        Any /v1-compatible API
   Commands / Keybindings        AgentOrchestrator                   Embeddings: Ollama only
   AttentionOverlay              ModelSelector + LLMRouter
   GutterHeatmap                 MultiAgentRunner          в†ђв†’  [Edit Genome Collector]
                                 ProjectMemoryGraph               SQLite + opt-in sync
                                 SemanticDriftDetector
                                 CausalDebugAgent
                                 CrossRepoIndexer
                                 VectorStore (vectra)
                                 AirGapModeManager
```

### Process 1: Extension Host (TypeScript)
- Registers commands, keybindings, sidebar, gutter decorations
- Hosts React WebView panels: Chat, Analytics, Tasks, Shards, Memory, Drift, Genome, Debug, Review
- Communicates with Sidecar via HTTP on localhost:39291
- Renders AttentionHeatmap overlay directly in editor gutter
- Reads/writes files via VS Code API only (never fs directly)

### Process 2: Sidecar Server (Node.js / Express)
- Runs as a child process spawned by the extension on activation
- Owns all heavy logic: indexing, shard assembly, agent orchestration
- Hosts ProjectMemoryGraph (persistent across sessions via SQLite)
- Hosts EditGenomeCollector (telemetry pipeline)
- Hosts MultiAgentRunner (parallel specialist agents)
- Hosts SemanticDriftDetector (tracks embedding drift on git commits)
- Hosts CausalDebugAgent (stack trace в†’ root cause analysis)
- Hosts CrossRepoIndexer (shared index across repositories)
- Exposes REST + SSE API consumed by Extension Host

### Process 3: LLM Backend (pluggable)
- **Gateway mode (default):** any OpenAI-compatible `/v1/chat/completions` endpoint via `OpenAICompatibleAdapter`
  - LiteLLM, vLLM, RunPod proxy, OpenAI, custom corporate gateway
  - Config: `neurocode.llm.apiBaseUrl`, `apiKey`, `model`
- **Ollama mode:** local `OllamaAdapter` when `neurocode.llm.mode = ollama`
- **Fallback:** optional `fallbackToOllama` when gateway unreachable
- **Embeddings:** always Ollama (`nomic-embed-text`) вЂ” never via gateway
- **Model selection:** `ModelSelector` вЂ” Auto picks model per task; Manual uses `selectedModel` from `GET /v1/models`
- All adapters implement the same `LLMAdapter` interface (`chat`, `stream`, `listModels`, `isAvailable`)

